<div id="review_1523222" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1523222" />
    <a title="Liza P." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/83576-liza-p"><img alt="Liza P." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1180153739p2/83576.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1523222?book_show_action=true">May 29, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Liza P." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Liza P." href="/user/show/83576-liza-p">Liza P.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780679431374" href="/book/show/18265.Gargantua_and_Pantagruel">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1523222" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17630953208026218946">I know that this crossed into the territory of heated historical debate... but technically this is the FIRST NOVEL ever written [or rather the first book that was written in that style].<br/><br/>Aside from that, this is just a beautiful, imaginative, slightly creepy book! One of my favorite books in the world!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


